[10:57] <dalek> parrot: be7c674 | (Andrew Aldridge)++ | / (5 files):
[10:57] <dalek> parrot: fix unix domain sockets
[10:57] <dalek> parrot:
[10:57] <dalek> parrot: It's not currently possible to bind an AF_UNIX socket because `getaddrinfo()`
[10:57] <dalek> parrot: and `getnameinfo()` don't work with AF_UNIX on all platforms.
[10:57] <dalek> parrot:
[10:57] <dalek> parrot: This patch does the following:
[10:57] <dalek> parrot: - Fix `getaddrinfo()` error reporting; it works via `gai_strerror()` rather
[10:57] <dalek> parrot:   than `errno`.
[10:57] <dalek> parrot: - Implement more error checking, preventing possible uninitialized reads if
[10:57] <dalek> parrot:   `getnameinfo()` fails.
[10:57] <dalek> parrot: - Implement special-cases for `Parrot_io_internal_getaddrinfo()` and
[10:57] <dalek> parrot:   `Parrot_io_internal_getnameinfo()` in the AF_UNIX case; on platforms
[10:57] <dalek> parrot:   without `sys/un.h`, these functions will now return an error if the socket
[10:57] <dalek> parrot:   family is (somehow) AF_UNIX.
[10:57] <dalek> parrot: - Implement some simple tests for working with Unix sockets.
[10:57] <dalek> parrot:
[10:57] <dalek> parrot: I couldn't get Parrot compiling with msvc on Windows, so I'm not completely
[10:57] <dalek> parrot: confident the platform conditional logic is correct.
